HEADWORD: Girasol
<hw>Gir"a*sol</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. <ets>girasole</ets>, or F. <ets>girasol</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>gyrare</ets> to turn around + <ets>sol</ets> sun.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>See <er>Heliotrope</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A variety of opal which is usually
milk white, bluish white, or sky blue; but in a bright light it reflects
a reddish color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

